{\pard\b\fs32 1. Introduction\par}
{\pard The FIDA Android app is a gamified fitness application designed to promote daily physical activity through real-time tracking, streaks, badges, and rewards. The app integrates GPS-based run tracking, step counting, water intake logging, sleep monitoring, and a comprehensive reward economy using XP, coins, and gems. Testing was performed on Android 12+ (API 31+) devices. Testing objectives include validating functional correctness, ensuring data consistency, UI responsiveness, and permission handling.\par}
{\pard\par}
{\pard\b\fs28 1.1 Scope\par}
{\pard The following modules are covered in this report:\par}
{\pard - Authentication (Login, Signup, Google Sign-In, Onboarding)\par}
{\pard - Profile Setup (3-step wizard)\par}
{\pard - GPS Run Tracking (PreRun, Countdown, Tracking, Summary)\par}
{\pard - Step Counter (Sensor service, daily baseline, Firestore sync)\par}
{\pard - Water Intake Tracker\par}
{\pard - Sleep Tracker\par}
{\pard - Gamification (XP, Coins, Gems, Badges, Streaks, Daily Rewards)\par}
{\pard - Shop & Power-Up System\par}
{\pard - Leaderboard\par}
{\pard - Settings (Account, Privacy, Notifications)\par}
{\pard - Navigation & Bottom Navigation Bar\par}
{\pard\par}
{\pard\b\fs28 1.2 Test Environment\par}
{\pard - Device: Android 12+ (API 31+), tested on Xiaomi device\par}
{\pard - Build: Debug APK, compileSdk 36, minSdk 28\par}
{\pard - Backend: Firebase Auth + Firestore + Realtime Database\par}
{\pard - Build command: ./gradlew.bat --no-daemon assembleDebug\par}
{\pard\par}
